<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"  TextAlignment="Justify"   xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">

<Paragraph>
Essential XlsIO supports to convert Excel data to JSON files by simply saving the workbook using the <Bold>SaveAsJson</Bold> method.
</Paragraph>

<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}">Features:</TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>

<List> 
<ListItem><Paragraph>Save as a simple JSON file or a JSON file with XML schema</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Save a workbook to JSON</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Save a worksheet to JSON</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Save a range to JSON</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Save as a stream with the above features</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>

